  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663095695020-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663095695020-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663095695020-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663095695020-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663095695020-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely dice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and cut your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682411261482-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682411261482-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682411261482-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682411261482-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1682411261482-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> lamb mince </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p><p>Divide the <strong>lamb mince</strong> into 3 per person and shape them into meatballs</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682411264419-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682411264419-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682411264419-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682411264419-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1682411264419-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced carrot </strong>and<strong> diced onion</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Top with the <strong>lamb meatballs</strong>, then put the dish in the oven for 10 min or until the meatballs are starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682411126725-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682411126725-x400.jpg",
